Japan Core Inflation Fell 0.2% Under Revised Method

-- B y   L i l y   N o n o m i y a
-- 
2011-08-12T08:55:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/japan-core-inflation-fell-0-2-under-revised-method-correct-.html
(Corrects to say prices fell, not rose in first paragraph.)  Japan ’s core consumer prices
excluding fresh food fell 0.2 percent under the government’s new
calculation method, compared with an earlier reading of 0.4
percent, the statistics bureau said in  Tokyo  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
